entry.name: Spike-in comparison
entry.description: Synthetic peptides were spiked in at different levels in a digested cell lysate from Streptococcus pyogenes

additional_fields.field: Synthetic peptides was spiked in at different levels in a trypsin digested cell lysate.

The raw data was converted to MGF and mzML using Proteowizard. The MGF files were searched using Mascot and X!Tandem and the search results were combined in Proteios. The results were exported in PRIDE XML format from Proteios.
No PTMs are included in the dataset
Bioinformatics Infrastructure for Life Sciences (BILS) network (Sweden)
Chawade A, Sandin M, Teleman J, Malmström J, Levander F. Data processing has major impact on the outcome of quantitative label-free LC-MS analysis. J Proteome Res. 2014 Nov 19
